I discovered Mezeh a few weeks ago. I must say that I was a fan of this location, its the only one I’ve tried.  This location is def under staffed, making the wait ridiculous. Sometimes 1 person is serving while the other 2 talk to each other instead of helping out.  A day ago I ordered the lamb bowl salad. A colleague of mine ordered the steak salad. We both put our own veggie variations on top. Fast forward a few hours and my co worker had intense cramps and had diarrhea as well as vomiting. I also ended up with extremely intense cramps and diarrhea. I think it’s obvious where made us both sick. Now I don’t know if because they are under staffed that they aren’t checking the food properly for expiration, or what! We both have been turned off of Mezeh for now.  I suggest the district manager go and check on them at PG Plaza. They need some help! Nothing worse than food poisoning on your lunch break.

We ordered 3 bowls via door dash. Delivery was excellent.  Unpacking our food, he first thing we noticed was that the bowls were not full and I am comparing them to what we received last month, which was the exact same order.  We were supposed to have 2 8 oz. basmati rice, they clearly  put the rice in 2 oz container, shorting us on a main ingredient. Sauce was missing, and the 2 that we did get, were half full containers.  We attempted to call Mezeh, but when you hit #5 to get a person, you get sent back to the beginning of the call menu.  There is no customer service number.  We want to support keeping businesses open and those working. We could have picked up our order but wanted to support those who make income delivering.  With that being said, I very much doubt I will be ordering again.  I would hope for some consistency, but there were too many mistakes.  There has always been some hesitation ordering online and having it delivered for this very reason.  We'll be waiting until we can go in person.
